        "subject": "LU-4856 misc: Reduce exposure to overflow on page counters.",
        "message": "LU-4856 misc: Reduce exposure to overflow on page counters.\n\nWhen the number of an object in use or circulation is tied to memory\nsize of the system, very large memory systems can overflow 32 bit\ncounters.  This patch addresses overflow on page counters in the osc\nLRU and obd accounting.\n\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/10537\nLustre-commit: e12bbee8207c41b2be5c8bb848f03bb81e75b025\n\nSigned-off-by: Stephen Champion <schamp@sgi.com>\nSigned-off-by: Gregoire Pichon <gregoire.pichon@bull.net>\nChange-Id: I90d143afd2932d87ee80cf3ae5bc04d3e58e667a\n"
      },
